               <msContents>
                  <summary>Lines 2-5 are the last lines of a page of the codex and contain the beginning of a new recipe which was continued at the top of the next page. Lines 6-10 contain a recipe for litchen-like skin eruptions, for which see the many compositions in Gal. XII 830-844.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
